<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="173" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,453,948]" pageId="4" pageNumber="173">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,525,551]" pageId="4" pageNumber="173">Distribution</emphasis>
. Atlantic, Pacific, Indian Oceans, and Mediterranean Sea (
<bibRefCitation author="Vinogradov, M. E. &amp; Volkov, A. F. &amp; Semenova, T. N." box="[1002,1266,526,553]" pageId="4" pageNumber="173" refId="ref16750" refString="Vinogradov, M. E., Volkov, A. F. &amp; Semenova, T. N. (1996) Hyperiid amphipods (Amphipoda, Hyperiidea) of the world oceans. Oxonian Press Pvt. Ltd., New Delhi, 632 pp." type="book" year="1996">
Vinogradov 
<emphasis box="[1143,1199,526,552]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="173">et al.</emphasis>
1996
</bibRefCitation>
). In the eastern Pacific from the Columbia River, 
<collectingCountry box="[530,589,562,588]" name="United States of America" pageId="4" pageNumber="173">USA</collectingCountry>
, to 
<collectingRegion box="[628,800,562,588]" country="Mexico" name="Baja California" pageId="4" pageNumber="173">Baja California</collectingRegion>
and off Cabo San Lucas, in the southern Gulf of 
<collectingRegion country="United States of America" name="California" pageId="4" pageNumber="173">California</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[199,285,598,624]" name="Mexico" pageId="4" pageNumber="173">Mexico</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Brusca, R. C. &amp; Hendrickx, M. E." box="[299,599,598,625]" pageId="4" pageNumber="173" pagination="139 - 154" refId="ref14339" refString="Brusca, R. C. &amp; Hendrickx, M. E. (2005) Cap. 12. Crustacea 4. Lophogastrida, Mysida, Amphipoda, Tanaidacea &amp; Cumacea. In: Hendrickx, M. E., Brusca, R. C. &amp; Findley L. T. (Eds.), A Distributional Checklist of the Macrofauna of the Gulf of California, Mexico. Part I. Invertebrates. [Listado y Distribucion de la Macrofauna del Golfo de California, Mexico, Parte I. Invertebrados]. Arizona-Sonora Desert Museum, Tucson, Arizona, pp. 139 - 154." type="book chapter" year="2005">Brusca &amp; Hendrickx 2005</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Garcia Madrigal, M. S." box="[610,862,598,624]" pageId="4" pageNumber="173" pagination="63 - 195" refId="ref14782" refString="Garcia Madrigal, M. S. (2007) Annotated checklist of the amphipods (Peracarida: Amphipoda) from the tropical eastern Pacific. Contributions to the Study of East Pacific Crustaceans, 4 (2), 63 - 195." type="journal article" year="2007">García Madrigal 2007</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="173" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,453,948]" pageId="4" pageNumber="173">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,634,660]" pageId="4" pageNumber="173">Remarks</emphasis>
. Commonly found in the Gulf of 
<collectingRegion box="[692,808,634,660]" country="United States of America" name="California" pageId="4" pageNumber="173">California</collectingRegion>
, particularly in the southern part (
<bibRefCitation author="Siegel-Causey, D." box="[1192,1424,634,660]" pageId="4" pageNumber="173" refId="ref16354" refString="Siegel-Causey, D. (1982) Factors determining the distribution of hyperiid Amphipoda in the Gulf of California. Ph. D. Thesis, University of Arizona, Tucson, Arizona, 535 pp." type="book" year="1982">Siegel-Causey 1982</bibRefCitation>
). Other records in the Gulf of 
<collectingRegion box="[464,578,670,696]" country="United States of America" name="California" pageId="4" pageNumber="173">California</collectingRegion>
are from 
<geoCoordinate box="[684,824,670,697]" degrees="23" direction="north" minutes="54" orientation="latitude" pageId="4" pageNumber="173" precision="15" seconds="27" value="23.9075">23°54’27”N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[834,989,670,696]" degrees="111" direction="west" minutes="20" orientation="longitude" pageId="4" pageNumber="173" precision="15" seconds="21" value="-111.33917">111°20’21”W</geoCoordinate>
and 
<geoCoordinate box="[1041,1181,670,697]" degrees="23" direction="north" minutes="50" orientation="latitude" pageId="4" pageNumber="173" precision="15" seconds="30" value="23.841667">23°50’30”N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[1192,1347,670,697]" degrees="111" direction="west" minutes="15" orientation="longitude" pageId="4" pageNumber="173" precision="15" seconds="45" value="-111.2625">111°15’45”W</geoCoordinate>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Garcia Madrigal, M. S." pageId="4" pageNumber="173" pagination="63 - 195" refId="ref14782" refString="Garcia Madrigal, M. S. (2007) Annotated checklist of the amphipods (Peracarida: Amphipoda) from the tropical eastern Pacific. Contributions to the Study of East Pacific Crustaceans, 4 (2), 63 - 195." type="journal article" year="2007">García Madrigal, 2007</bibRefCitation>
). Mostly epipelagic and partly mesopelagic (surface to 
<quantity box="[950,1080,706,732]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="173" unit="m" value="250.0" valueMax="300.0" valueMin="200.0">200‒300 m</quantity>
), occasionally deeper (
<quantity metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="173" unit="m" value="550.0" valueMax="600.0" valueMin="500.0">500‒600 m</quantity>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Vinogradov, M. E. &amp; Volkov, A. F. &amp; Semenova, T. N." box="[197,463,742,769]" pageId="4" pageNumber="173" refId="ref16750" refString="Vinogradov, M. E., Volkov, A. F. &amp; Semenova, T. N. (1996) Hyperiid amphipods (Amphipoda, Hyperiidea) of the world oceans. Oxonian Press Pvt. Ltd., New Delhi, 632 pp." type="book" year="1996">
Vinogradov 
<emphasis box="[339,396,742,768]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="173">et al.</emphasis>
1996
</bibRefCitation>
). According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Garcia Madrigal, M. S." box="[636,903,742,768]" pageId="4" pageNumber="173" pagination="63 - 195" refId="ref14782" refString="Garcia Madrigal, M. S. (2007) Annotated checklist of the amphipods (Peracarida: Amphipoda) from the tropical eastern Pacific. Contributions to the Study of East Pacific Crustaceans, 4 (2), 63 - 195." type="journal article" year="2007">García Madrigal (2007)</bibRefCitation>
this species occurs between surface and 
<quantity box="[1365,1436,742,768]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.8" pageId="4" pageNumber="173" unit="m" value="680.0">680 m</quantity>
depth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,453,948]" pageId="4" pageNumber="173">
The specimens examined are partially damaged and somewhat transparent, but shows the main distinctive characteristic of the species, i.e., eyes limited to the upper part of the head, and dactyls of PV to PVII shorter than in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Stebbing" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[151,287,886,912]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lestrigonidae" genus="Hyperioides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="4" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sibaginis">
